sentences: Dexter Edge (born in Tacoma, Washington, 20 January 1953) is an American musicologist.
He studied music history at the University of Southern California (1983-2001, Ph.D., 2001).
He has taught music history at the Louisiana State University 1997-1999.
2002-2005 he was Senior Editor at the Packard Humanities Institute (The Complete Works of Carl Philip Emanuel Bach).
He was a 2006 Fellow of the American Council of Learned Societies, and the "William J. Bouwsma" Fellow at the National Humanities Center (2006-2007).
Since 2014, he has collaborated with David Black on an online edition in progress of newly discovered Mozart documents.
